,{"ana":36},"#condition.damaged",{"layout":38},{"p":39,"rs":40,"damage":44},"Text not quite perpendicular to the stone, four full lines of text, with final line centred.",{"_":41,"ana":42,"ref":43},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"ana":45},"#text_condition.incomplete",{"lettering":47,"dimensions":48},"lunate epsilon and sigma, uncial omega, delta with extended hasta, use of supralines.",[49,54],{"type":50,"l":51,"from":52,"to":52,"unit":53},"letterHeight","Line 1","line1","mm",{"type":55,"l":56,"from":52,"to":57,"unit":53},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2","line2",{"_":59,"notBefore":60,"notAfter":61},"6th century CE",501,600,[63,67],{"_":64,"type":65,"ref":66,"region":64},"Sicilia","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462492",{"_":68,"type":69,"ref":70,"region":64},"Sicily","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2523119",[],[],"Unknown","",{"_":76,"mainLang":77,"languages":78},"Ancient Greek","grc",[76],"644938",[],[82,83,83,84,85,86,87],"L'année épigraphique: revue des publications épigraphiques relatives a l'antiquité romaine., 1888-","Supplementum epigraphicum graecum, 1923-","Bulletin épigraphique, 1888-","Manganaro, 2005, Per la storia della Sicilia bilingue in epoca tardoantica: presbiteri cristiani e superstizione giudaizzante nel contado","Manganaro Perrone, 2006, Epigrafe in greco di IV sec. d.C. di Alesa (Sicilia) in versi e prosa, per la morte di Eirena Philandros, \"carissima a Botis boio-celtico\"","Rizzone, 2009, Iscrizioni tardoantiche da Mineo (CT)",[89,90,90,91,92,93,94],"R46KDTZX","F2GG87EQ","77P5MNIR","XRJWG8D3","6KPB9V5B","P44QBETH",[96,97,98,21,25,29,99,100,99,100,101,102,77],"isic003461","epitaph of gregorios",{"_":12},"sicilia","sicily","unknown","ancient greek","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[ἐν]θάδε κῆτε ὡ ἐν μακαρίᾳ \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[μ]νήμῃ \u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Γρηγώριος υἱὸς Πο\n                    \">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Γρηγώριος\">Γρηγώριος\u003C/span> υἱὸς \u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Πο\n                    \">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Πο\n                    \">\u003Cspan data-text=\"Πο\">Πο\u003C/span>-\u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span> του π\u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">ρ\u003C/span>(εσ)\u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">β\u003C/span>(υτέρου) ζήσας ἔτη κβ´ \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[τ(ελ)]ευτᾷ δὲ ἐν \u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">Κ\u003C/span>(υρί)\u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">ῳ\u003C/span> μηνὴ Ἰ\u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">ου\u003C/span>(λίῳ) \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>ἰν\u003Cspan class=\"intraline\" title=\"line through\">δ\u003C/span>(ικτιῶνος) η´ \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"author":3,"date":4,"citedRange":105,"ptr":106,"ref":108,"inscriptionDate":4,"title":2,"citation":5,"uri":6,"year":4},"92 n.20",{"target":107},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/6KPB9V5B",{"_":109,"target":109},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001787",2006,{"file":112,"uri":112,"title":113,"status":114,"editionAuthor":116,"type":117,"objectType":118,"material":119,"condition":74,"layoutDesc":127,"handNote":131,"date":212,"places":217,"geo":225,"country":64,"provenance":219,"provenanceGeo":229,"region":68,"settlement":219,"repository":232,"idno":236,"textLang":239,"tmNumber":241,"facsimile":242,"letterHeights":249,"publications":287,"zotero":290,"keywords":293,"html":301,"bibl":302,"bulletinDateSort":110,"citedRangeSort":305,"languageSort":76,"materialSort":120,"typeSort":21},"ISic003337","Funerary inscription for Eirena",{"_":115},"edited",null,{"_":21,"ana":22,"ref":23},{"_":25,"ana":26,"ref":27},{"_":120,"ana":121,"type":122,"subtype":123,"resp":126,"ref":34},"Very fine-grained, veined, white marble, likely Pavonazzetto, Docimian. Digital microscopy: indistinguishable fabric. Scribbly veins, maybe a limestone (identification based on pXRF, digital microscopy)","#material.inorganic.stone.metamorphic_rock.marble.Pavonazzetto #material.inorganic.stone.metamorphic_rock.marble.calcitic_marble.Docimian","stone.marble",[124,125],"Pavonazzetto","Docimian","#Coccato",{"layout":128},{"p":129,"rs":130,"damage":74},"Ten lines of Greek filling the available space, decreasing notably in size in the second five lines",{"_":41,"ana":42,"ref":43},{"lettering":132,"dimensions":133},"The letters are engraved in a fairly plain, square fashion, with simple serifs. Alpha is mostly with broken bar, sometimes with an extended upper serif, although there is a straight bar example in line 7 and in lines 8 and 10 straight bar descending to left foot; beta is closed, with larger lower eye, generally horizontal along the base; delta varies between regular triangle and oblique lower bar with extended serif above; epsilon has straight bars of equal length, except for instances in lines 9 and 10 when it is lunate; theta is ovoid with connecting straight bar; kappa has short tails; lambda sometimes has an extended upper serif; mu varies between a form with vertical first and last hastae and short middle strokes meeting above the line and cursive form comparable to a lower-case mu in line 9; omicron is full size in the first few lines, but increasingly is smaller and mid-line; sigma is consistently lunate, but more often formed of three straight strokes; less often a single curved stroke; omega is consistently lunate, and sometimes smaller and mid-line. The eta and nu are in ligature in lines 5, 6 and 7. In line 5 the omicron in the final word is inscribed above the other letters (due to omission?). The last two/three words of the last line are enclosed between a pair of christograms. Small hedera occur in lines 1, 3, 5, and 10.",[134,138,143,148,153,156,162,167,172,177,183,186,190,193,197,201,203,207,210],{"type":50,"l":51,"from":52,"to":52,"h":135,"unit":53,"atLeast":136,"atMost":137},"12-18","12","18",{"type":50,"l":139,"from":57,"to":57,"h":140,"unit":53,"atLeast":141,"atMost":142},"Line 2","14-19","14","19",{"type":50,"l":144,"from":145,"to":145,"h":146,"unit":53,"atLeast":136,"atMost":147},"Line 3","line3","12-22","22",{"type":50,"l":149,"from":150,"to":150,"h":151,"unit":53,"atLeast":152,"atMost":147},"Line 4","line4","8-22","8",{"type":50,"l":154,"from":155,"to":155,"h":135,"unit":53,"atLeast":136,"atMost":137},"Line 5","line5",{"type":50,"l":157,"from":158,"to":158,"h":159,"unit":53,"atLeast":160,"atMost":161},"Line 6","line6","9-16","9","16",{"type":50,"l":163,"from":164,"to":164,"h":165,"unit":53,"atLeast":166,"atMost":141},"Line 7","line7","7-14","7",{"type":50,"l":168,"from":169,"to":169,"h":170,"unit":53,"atLeast":171,"atMost":136},"Line 8","line8","6-12","6",{"type":50,"l":173,"from":174,"to":174,"h":175,"unit":53,"atLeast":171,"atMost":176},"Line 9","line9","6-10","10",{"type":50,"l":178,"from":179,"to":179,"h":180,"unit":53,"atLeast":181,"atMost":182},"Line 10","line10","5-13","5","13",{"type":55,"l":56,"from":52,"to":57,"h":184,"unit":53,"atLeast":176,"atMost":185},"10-15","15",{"type":55,"l":187,"from":57,"to":145,"h":188,"unit":53,"atLeast":189,"atMost":166},"Interlineation line 2 to 3","3-7","3",{"type":55,"l":191,"from":145,"to":150,"h":192,"unit":53,"atLeast":181,"atMost":185},"Interlineation line 3 to 4","5-15",{"type":55,"l":194,"from":150,"to":155,"h":195,"unit":53,"atLeast":196,"atMost":176},"Interlineation line 4 to 5","4-10","4",{"type":55,"l":198,"from":155,"to":158,"h":199,"unit":53,"atLeast":200,"atMost":166},"Interlineation line 5 to 6","2-7","2",{"type":55,"l":202,"from":158,"to":164,"h":199,"unit":53,"atLeast":200,"atMost":166},"Interlineation line 6 to 7",{"type":55,"l":204,"from":164,"to":169,"h":205,"unit":53,"atLeast":206,"atMost":171},"Interlineation line 7 to 8","1-6","1",{"type":55,"l":208,"from":169,"to":174,"h":209,"unit":53,"atLeast":206,"atMost":181},"Interlineation line 8 to 9","1-5",{"type":55,"l":211,"from":174,"to":179,"h":209,"unit":53,"atLeast":206,"atMost":181},"Interlineation line 9 to 10",{"_":213,"notBefore":214,"notAfter":215,"evidence":216},"5th century CE, with a likely terminus post quem of 403-408 CE, given that a coin of that date was found within the tomb (Tigano 2009: 164; more generally, the tombs of this part of the necropolis all date late 4th to 5th century CE)",403,500,"archaeological-context",[218,221],{"_":219,"type":65,"ref":220,"region":64},"Halaesa","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462225",{"_":222,"type":69,"ref":223,"offset":224,"region":64},"Castel di Tusa","http://sws.geonames.org/2525099","near",[226],[227,228],37.99907,14.26197,[230,231],38.0073241,14.2527381,{"_":233,"role":234,"ref":235},"Antiquarium e sito archeologico di Halaesa ","museum","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/053",{"_":237,"type":238},"ME 20272","inventory",{"_":76,"mainLang":77,"languages":240},[76],"645584",{"n":243,"url":244,"height":245,"width":246,"desc":247,"surfaceType":248},"screen","ISic003337_tiled.tif","3387px","5310px","Photo J. Prag courtesy Soprintendenza BBCCAA di Messina","front",[250,253,256,258,260,261,264,266,268,270,273,275,277,278,280,282,283,285,286],{"atLeast":251,"atMost":252},12,18,{"atLeast":254,"atMost":255},14,19,{"atLeast":251,"atMost":257},22,{"atLeast":259,"atMost":257},8,{"atLeast":251,"atMost":252},{"atLeast":262,"atMost":263},9,16,{"atLeast":265,"atMost":254},7,{"atLeast":267,"atMost":251},6,{"atLeast